The paper deals with stochastic control in a noisy environment, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) concepts. The paper also discusses the causality relationship and the evolution of the system, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new analysis that involves entropy, which is a central concept in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
